                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17490906-85-off347 t17490906-85-crimeloc349"></join>, being a little in liquor, I went to lie down on a bed where the prisoner Downing lay; he said, you had better take off your cloaths; I took off my coat, and laid myself down with my breeches and stockings on; he got up when I was sleeping, and took away my coat; I never saw my coat since, but here is a pawnbroker, who has got the buttons, which was brought to him by the prisoner Downing; I believe Crosby is innocent of the affair.</p>
